comments: Gravett (ORL) legally contests Mills' (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Wagner (ORL) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Griffin (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Harris (ORL) and absorbs the contact.
Lopez (ORL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Mills (BKN) and the arm contact is marginal.
Lopez (ORL) places a hand on Griffin's (BKN) back with slight extension as he sets the pick but the contact is marginal.
Okeke (ORL) blocks the shot attempt by Duke Jr. (BKN) before it hits the backboard.
Mills (BKN) makes contact to Wagner's (ORL) arm that affects his ability to pass.
Edwards (BKN) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Griffin (BKN) has his hand on the ball and Wagner (ORL) is able to move through it and maintain possession during his driving shot attempt.  Any contact is incidental.
Harris (ORL) is out of bounds while in possession of the ball.
Lopez (ORL) legally contests Mills' (BKN) jump shot attempt and avoids making any contact.  The two players make incidental foot contact once Mills has returned to the floor.
Thomas (BKN) commits a take foul on Wagner (ORL).
Lopez (ORL) legally contests Griffin's (BKN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Duke Jr. (BKN) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
